body:
We might want to make the thresholding more configurable: I want to gather
some real experience first however.

On Tue, Mar 28, 2017 at 8:55 AM Noah Eisen <notifications@github.com> wrote:

> *@ncteisen* approved this pull request.
>
> Cool!
> ------------------------------
>
> In tools/profiling/microbenchmarks/bm_diff.py
> <https://github.com/grpc/grpc/pull/10336#discussion_r108459682>:
>
> > +    }
> +    self.final = {}
> +
> +  def add_sample(self, data, new):
> +    for f in _INTERESTING:
> +      if f in data:
> +        self.samples[new][f].append(float(data[f]))
> +
> +  def process(self):
> +    for f in _INTERESTING:
> +      new = self.samples[True][f]
> +      old = self.samples[False][f]
> +      if not new or not old: continue
> +      p = stats.ttest_ind(new, old)[1]
> +      delta = avg(new) - avg(old)
> +      if p < args.p_threshold and abs(delta) > 0.1:
>
> Would we ever want to toggle the delta threshold via flags?
>
